427
00:38:43,619 --> 00:38:44,619
Now here's a funny statement.

428
00:38:44,639 --> 00:38:47,503
This is why Noreen emailed me.

429
00:38:47,643 --> 00:38:49,686
Anger, greed and delusion are all known.

430
00:38:50,188 --> 00:38:58,358
Now here I'm presuming that she's actually meaning that she sees anger, greed and delusion in other people.

431
00:38:59,139 --> 00:39:00,722
And that it's not affecting her.

432
00:39:00,802 --> 00:39:02,304
It's not coming into her.

433
00:39:02,684 --> 00:39:06,789
I'm presuming that she hasn't got that within her.

434
00:39:06,989 --> 00:39:16,742
because it wouldn't make sense for her to have that within her as such, because she's undercut the whole process by destroying that wrong identity from which it all arises.

435
00:39:19,445 --> 00:39:21,728
But I did suggest to Nodin something else.

436
00:39:24,413 --> 00:39:36,168
You'll know that there are these four levels of sanctity, of spiritual attainment, the stream-enterer, and then the once-returner, the non-returner, and the arahat.

437
00:39:36,637 --> 00:39:47,773
Now, normally speaking, the way it's normally understood, the way the commentaries would normally put it, is that there's a Magga and a Pala, the path and the fruit.

438
00:39:48,293 --> 00:39:55,882
And it's normally said that when a person becomes a Sotapanna, there is a moment, that initial moment, is the path.

439
00:39:56,324 --> 00:40:02,572
And then all the other moments of their lives, as a Sotapanna, is the fruit of that insight.

440
00:40:04,253 --> 00:40:04,755
Now...

441
00:40:05,123 --> 00:40:33,594
and that's the same for them all but there's definitely evidence in the scriptures to say that actually these are two paths and this makes great sense to me personally the first one is to do with the right understanding you see where a person sees quite clearly one of these three characteristics and the seeing of these characteristics now has to be

442
00:40:33,793 --> 00:41:03,108
become systemic it has to run through right attitude right speech right action right livelihood it has to manifest outwards that way and until it's done that totally we can't talk about the fruit of it so one of the arguments for that is the experience the Buddha himself had where it's said in the scriptures he has this moment of enlightenment but then Mara chases him remember for seven years

443
00:41:03,476 --> 00:41:13,085
with his three daughters, sensual pleasure, eroticism and boredom.

444
00:41:13,585 --> 00:41:16,929
We can see that that's where his problems lay.

445
00:41:18,809 --> 00:41:20,132
He wasn't so much in power.

446
00:41:20,552 --> 00:41:24,014
If you remember, Jesus was tempted by power.

447
00:41:24,394 --> 00:41:26,097
He's saying to the top of the mountain about the devil.

448
00:41:26,996 --> 00:41:28,259
You can have all this, you see.

449
00:41:28,818 --> 00:41:32,202
So there's always power, riches and sensuality.

450
00:41:33,615 --> 00:41:36,498
So that was where you might say he'd been stuck, you might say.

451
00:41:36,920 --> 00:41:41,324
So seven years, Mara finally gives up on it.

452
00:41:41,945 --> 00:41:43,648
Says, he sees me, Mara sees me.

453
00:41:44,307 --> 00:41:49,034
But the purity had not become systemic.

454
00:41:49,054 --> 00:41:50,155
There's a suggestion there.

455
00:41:50,175 --> 00:41:51,956
Whether it was seven years or not, who knows?

456
00:41:52,398 --> 00:42:03,150
But there's an understanding there that it took time for this huge insight, for this new liberation to find its way through all his habits,

457
00:42:03,501 --> 00:42:11,753
And because his habits were still there, he would have seen them as unwholesome.

458
00:42:11,775 --> 00:42:20,748
So it may be that that's also what she's referring to, and she's not yet reached the fruit of her insight.

459
00:42:21,268 --> 00:42:29,981
But I prefer to see it the other way, that she has actually, and that she's quite aware when somebody's being greedy, deluded, she's not fooled by it.

460
00:42:32,003 --> 00:42:34,025
But what a wonderful thing to be able to say.

461
00:42:34,065 --> 00:42:37,972
I'm unable to detect even an instant when they have power.

462
00:42:38,512 --> 00:42:40,436
Any power over my heart.

463
00:42:41,117 --> 00:42:42,338
I want to be able to say that.

464
00:42:44,523 --> 00:42:46,065
Yes, they arise and cease.

465
00:42:46,184 --> 00:42:47,347
They are forever changing.

466
00:42:47,728 --> 00:42:51,634
But the presence that knows them never changes for an instant.

467
00:42:53,076 --> 00:42:54,197
Never changes for an instant.

468
00:42:54,778 --> 00:42:59,226
And we can get a hint of that in ourselves because when you

469
00:42:59,492 --> 00:43:10,061
finally, when you've isolated the sense of the observer very clearly in yourself, and then you reflect at the end of your sitting or something, what was it like to be there?

470
00:43:10,501 --> 00:43:12,184
What's inside the observer?

471
00:43:12,204 --> 00:43:13,204
What's it made of?

472
00:43:18,208 --> 00:43:24,353
And that's where we're getting a hint that where the Buddha says, those who are mindful in this way are in the presence of Nibbana.

473
00:43:25,175 --> 00:43:29,077
He's not actually saying that we can't get a taste for it, we can't get a

474
00:43:29,226 --> 00:43:31,030
a feel for it.

475
00:43:31,050 --> 00:43:40,262
And it's important because the more we get that feel for it, the silence of it, the lack of excitement.

476
00:43:40,563 --> 00:43:47,693
Our happiness is always gauged by how happy we are emotionally, how excited we are, what the future has to offer us.

477
00:43:48,315 --> 00:43:55,365
And yet here there's a pointing to some sort of stasis, some sort of peacefulness that never changes.

478
00:43:56,266 --> 00:43:59,030
An internal...

479
00:43:59,331 --> 00:44:28,072
position of silence you know and when we when we begin to sense that it's also begin to realize that it's not part of this process of arising and passing away it is forever there you see now that's very difficult for us to to grasp because for us there is time we can't imagine something not being in time not being caught up in some sort of changing process yeah

480
00:44:29,538 --> 00:44:30,659
But she's pointing to that.

481
00:44:30,679 --> 00:44:32,322
She's forever unborn and undying.

482
00:44:32,362 --> 00:44:36,887
It's not part of this process of the phenomenal world.

483
00:44:37,449 --> 00:44:40,572
And then finally, just this is the end of suffering.

484
00:44:44,117 --> 00:44:51,748
May it be that Meichi Kyo has inspired us, driven us to greater efforts.

485
00:44:52,670 --> 00:44:59,358
May we all be fully realized and free from all suffering sooner rather than later.

486
00:45:02,139 --> 00:45:02,969
Sadhu.

487
00:45:04,061 --> 00:45:04,911
Sadhu.

